<h1>Getting Started</h1>

<h2>Ember CLI</h2>
<ol>
    <li>
        <p><i>optional:</i> Create an app if you don't have one already.</p>
        <pre><code class="bash">ember init</code></pre>
    </li>
    <li>
        <p>Install the components addon<p>
        <pre><code class="bash">npm install --save-dev ember-cli-components</code></pre>
    </li>
</ol>

<h2>Manual</h2>

<ol>
    <li>
        <p>Installing via <i>bower</i> is the simplest form:</p>
        <pre><code class="bash">bower install ember-components</code></pre>
    </li>
    <li>
    <p><i>recommended (but not required): </i>Include Bootstrap for styling as most components are already styled for Bootstrap.</p>
        <pre><code class="html">&lt;link href="//netdna.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/3.0.0/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet"&gt;</code></pre>
    </li>
    <li>
        <p>Include Ember Component (and its dependencies)</p>
        <pre><code class="html">&lt;script src="bower_components/ember-components/dist/globals/main.js"&gt;
&lt;script src="bower_components/ember-utils/dist/globals/main.js"&gt;
&lt;script src="bower_components/ic-styled/main.js"&gt;</script></code></pre>
        <b>Note:</b> If you want other options then importing the entire library globally take a look at: <a href="https://github.com/indexiatech/ember-components/tree/master/dist">dist folder</a>
    </li>
</ol>

<p>Of course you need jquery, ember.js and handlebars included in your project too.</p>


